&lt;h1 id=&#34;wip-ansible-lint&#34;&gt;WIP: Ansible Lint&lt;/h1&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Petar Šlat&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-is-ansible-lint&#34;&gt;What is ansible-lint?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The project was originally started by @willthames, and has since been transferred to the Ansible project team.
Check the guy out at &lt;a href=&#34;https://willthames.github.io/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;https://willthames.github.io/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-do-we-start-using-it&#34;&gt;How do we start using it?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;pip install ansible-lint
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-can-we-lint&#34;&gt;What can we lint?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any playbook or role&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;why-do-we-need-to-do-it&#34;&gt;Why do we need to do it?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Because one day in the near future we will be our own father.
And we want to share our roles with others&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;share-our-roles&#34;&gt;Share our roles?&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yes, there is scoring system for Ansible Galaxy and ansible-lint is being used there&lt;/p&gt;

